This paper is about a technique for finding security bugs in programs that process structured inputs, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also introduces a grammar-aware trimming strategy and two grammar-aware mutation strategies, which are techniques that are commonly used in software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). Additionally, the paper evaluates the effectiveness of the proposed approach on real-life large-scale programs, which is a topic that falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper uses machine learning techniques to improve the effectiveness of the approach, which is a topic that falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
